MASTER DOCUMENT GENERATION — BUILD RULES

THIS TEMPLATE PRODUCES A FULL ARC DOCUMENT MADE OF:
• PAGE 1 (ARC TITLE + ARC DESCRIPTION)
• PAGE 2+ (SECTION PAGES — each section is its own page)
• Section pages repeat this exact structure for every section in the arc.

------------------------------------------------------------
PAGE 1 — ARC TITLE + ARC DESCRIPTION — BUILD RULES
------------------------------------------------------------

INPUT FIELDS:
• ARC Name
• ARC Description

OUTPUT STRUCTURE (exact):
ARC TITLE:  [ARC Name]

Description:  [ARC Description paragraph(s)]

FORMATTING RULES:
• ARC TITLE appears first, bolded, followed by a colon, then a line break, then the ARC Name on the next line.
• The word “Description:” appears exactly as written, bolded, followed by a colon.
• The ARC Description text appears immediately after “Description:” on the same line.
• No extra commentary, no additional sentences, no generated embellishments.
• Use the ARC Name and Description exactly as provided in raw input.


------------------------------------------------------------
PAGE 2+ — SECTION PAGE — BUILD RULES
------------------------------------------------------------

INPUT FIELDS PER SECTION:
• Section Number (integer)
• Section Title (text)
• Section Description (one sentence per micro-rules)
• Section Benefit (one sentence per micro-rules)

INPUT FIELDS FOR ALL JUMPS:
(These may be supplied separately from section list)
For each jump (per line):
• Jump Title
• Jump Type
• Jump Description
• Jump Benefit (may contain multiple sentences)
• Jump Section Reference (ex: "Section 2: Learning That Sticks")

PARSING RULES:
• Jump numbering is assigned automatically based on sequence order.
• Jump numbering continues from arc start (so Section 2 begins where Section 1 ended).
• Jumps for each section are determined by matching Section Reference text.
• Jumps are always printed in the exact order they are provided in the jump dataset.

OUTPUT STRUCTURE (exact):

Section [Section Number]: [Section Title]  
Description: [Section Description]  
Benefit: [Section Benefit]

Jump [jump number]  
[Jump Title]  
Jump Type: [Jump Type]  
Description: [Jump Description]  
Benefit: [Jump Benefit]

(then repeat Jump block for all jumps belonging to that section)

FORMATTING RULES:
• Do not rewrite or edit any user-provided text.
• Preserve all capitalization and punctuation exactly.
• Benefit may be multiple sentences exactly as provided.
• Each field prints exactly as shown above.
• No commentary or extra sentences outside this structure.
